  css: '...'
})

// This will not work
Ractive({
  css: '...'
})  From 0.9.4 , if  css  is a function, the function will be called with a handle to the component's style data and is expected to return a string of CSS.  const Component = Ractive.extend({
  css(data) {
    // you can use Ractive.styleSet('colors.special', 'pink') or Component.styleSet('colors.special', 'pink')
    // at any time to override the default here, which is green
    return `
      .super-special { color: ${data('colors.special') || 'green'}; }
    `
  }
})

(Object string, any |Function)  The data for an instance, or default data for a component. Can either be an object or a function that returns an object.  // Object form
